{
  "stem": "11882.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father was a Catholic, and my mother was a-- a Protestant.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Catholics were regarded as-- in this little Protestant town-- as rather-- something not quite understood, and not wanted, particularly.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was really a-- [LAUGHS] a mixed marriage, you can say.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father-- at that time, the Catholic church was very conservative-- had to swear he would bring any ensuing children from the marriage up as Catholics.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my mother always planned to keep the little one, at least, to go to church with her.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But she was rather a little tired with all her family work, and never managed to get up on Sunday and take her off.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] So yes, I'd say my father was a good Catholic.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, through our school, of course.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In those days, it was not illegal to read from the Old Testament.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We knew the Old Testament in our public school almost by heart.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And today, I guess it's illegal.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But at any rate, I don't know whether you would call it religious, but the fascinating stories of the Old Testament are well known to all who went to school in the simple schools and public schools in those days.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then, my mother wanted me to be a blonde.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I had dark hair.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she saw a beautiful blonde neighbor, a French girl-- French by derivation-- Blanche.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Blanche St.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Pierre was a beautiful blonde girl of 18-- and she wanted me to become beautiful like that when I was 18, and sent me to a strict Catholic school, Nazareth Academy.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I didn't turn blonde, of course.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I went eight years to these Catholic schools, very-- I would say classical, high-level education.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They turned me into a Latin teacher, unemployed Latin teacher.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
